response.Q0: In the first few turns I was clicking the nodes closest to the spider and trying to find the most profitable path. Quickly I realised that the most important node was the outermost nodes so I just started clicking on these. If one of theses nodes was +30 or higher I would accept and make the path towards it.
response.Q1: I only changed my strategy once after the first 5 or so turns (see above). After this my strategy remained the same.
response.Q2: It was quite obvious to me what the correct strategy was. As there was no information given on the real cash bonus I would receive I was happy to just make a of profit $30 and above on each turn.
